<br>
After reading the numerous posts about how rewarding it was to solo bloodgills in Lake of Ill Omen, I decided I would reach 49 there. As a 47 magician I found my way to the edge of the lake and bound myself. Summoned three waterstones and was off.<br>
<br>
After starting to fight the goblins I developed a strategy:<br>
1)I summoned Fire pet <br>
2)I would buff pet and myself<br>
3) med for mana if needed and then send pet at the double spawn<br>
4)after sending pet I heal him once, assist, nuke, and then heal again, assist against other bloodgill and nuke it.<br>
..now usually this strategy is incredible, but time and time again they are just killing off my pet without warning or my nuke isnt working at all. One fizzle and I'm destroyed (after specializing in evocation too!) Any advice to better my chances of making sure I survive because I have lost nearly a level and a half through pathetic deaths not only because of lag but also minior mishaps that kill my pet and I.<br>
<br>
Also can anyone clue me in to who the Bloodgill Maurader is? He has too killed me once on occasion (back when I tried the ground floor), thanks everyone<br>
<br>
